# Styling Guidelines
Do not use purple/blue gradients or colors as the primary color.

## CSS Organization

- Use separate CSS files for component-specific styles
- Keep global styles in `index.css` or `App.css`
- Group related styles together with comments
- Use consistent spacing and indentation (2 spaces)

## Naming Conventions

Use BEM-like naming with kebab-case:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
.app-header { }
.text-box-controls { }
.upload-label { }
.upload-label:hover { }

/* ❌ BAD */
.appHeader { }
.textBoxControls { }
.upload_label { }
```

## Best Practices

### Avoid Inline Styles

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div style={{ color: 'red', padding: '10px' }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="error-message">
```

### Use CSS Classes

- Prefer CSS classes over inline styles
- Use semantic class names that describe purpose, not appearance
- Group related styles logically

### Responsive Design

Always include responsive breakpoints:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .app-content {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .app-header {
    padding: 1rem;
  }
}
```

### Transitions and Interactions

Add smooth transitions for interactive elements:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
.upload-label {
  transition: background-color 0.2s;
}

.upload-label:hover {
  background-color: #2980b9;
}
```

### Color Usage

- Use consistent color palette
- Define colors with hex values or CSS variables
- Use semantic color names in comments if needed

### Spacing

- Use rem units for spacing (padding, margin)
- Maintain consistent spacing scale (0.5rem, 0.75rem, 1rem, 1.5rem, 2rem)
- Use flexbox/grid gaps for component spacing

### Focus States

Always include focus states for accessibility:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
.url-input:focus {
  outline: none;
  border-color: #3498db;
}
```
